# Literature Review: Determinants of Emerging Technologies Adoption in the South African Financial

Sector

## Introduction

The adoption of emerging technologies is crucial for organizations to stay competitive and achieve growth
in today's digital era. Understanding the determinants of technology adoption is essential for the successful
implementation and utilization of these technologies in various sectors, including the financial sector. This
literature review aims to explore the determinants of emerging technologies adoption in the South African
financial sector, synthesizing the findings from relevant research studies.

## Theory of Planned Behaviour (TPB) and Cryptocurrency Adoption

One research study by Mutambara (2019) applied the Theory of Planned Behaviour (TPB) to predict the
behavioural intention to adopt cryptocurrency in South Africa. The TPB suggests that attitude, subjective
norm, and perceived behavioural control influence an individual's intention to adopt a specific behaviour.
The findings of the study indicated that attitude and perceived behavioural control had a positive impact
on the intention to adopt cryptocurrency. However, subjective norm showed a negative non-significant
influence (Mutambara, 2019).

## Cloud Computing Adoption in Saudi Healthcare Organizations

While the specific focus of the research study by Alharbi, Atkins, and Stanier (2016) was on cloud
computing adoption in Saudi healthcare organizations, some of the findings can be relevant to the adoption
of emerging technologies in the South African financial sector. The study identified several determinants
of cloud computing adoption, including perceived benefits, perceived risks, organizational readiness, top
management support, and IT infrastructure. The findings highlighted the significance of these determinants in influencing the adoption decision and successful implementation of cloud computing (Alharbi,
Atkins, & Stanier, 2016).

## Synthesis and Integration of Findings

Integrating the findings from Mutambara's (2019) study on cryptocurrency adoption and Alharbi et
al.'s (2016) study on cloud computing adoption, it can be inferred that attitude, perceived benefits, and
perceived risks play crucial roles in determining the adoption of emerging technologies in the financial
sector. The positive impact of attitude and perceived behavioural control found in the cryptocurrency
adoption study aligns with the importance of perceived benefits and organizational readiness identified in
the cloud computing adoption study.
